        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 4:21PM CDT by NWS Lubbock TX</headline>
        <description>At 420 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles south of Black, or 9 miles east of Friona, moving east at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dimmitt, Easter, and Black.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
